VALUES
(54, 1, 1, 56, 1, 3, 3, 'commandment of God our Saviour', 'Connection of Apostolic Commandment', 'Both passages emphasize the ''commandment of God our Saviour,'' highlighting the authority behind Paul''s and Titus''s ministry. This connection underscores the shared divine mandate in their roles as apostles.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 1, 51, 1, 27, 27, NULL, 'Connection of Hope in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize Christ as the source of hope. In 1 Timothy, Paul refers to Jesus as ''our hope,'' while Colossians highlights ''Christ in you, the hope of glory.'' This connection highlights the centrality of Christ in the believer''s hope.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 1, 44, 9, 15, 15, 'apostle of Jesus Christ', 'Paul''s Apostolic Mission', 'This connection highlights Paul''s role as a chosen vessel, as indicated in both passages. In 1 Timothy, Paul identifies himself as an apostle, while Acts emphasizes his mission to bear the name of Jesus before various groups.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 1, 65, 1, 25, 25, 'God our Saviour', 'Connection of God as Saviour', 'Both passages emphasize God as Saviour, highlighting His authority and majesty. This connection underscores the role of God in salvation and His divine attributes.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 1, 48, 1, 1, 1, 'an apostle of Jesus Christ', 'Connection of Apostolic Authority', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s role as an apostle appointed by divine authority. They highlight that his apostleship is not derived from human sources but directly from Jesus Christ and God.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 1, 54, 1, 12, 12, 'apostle of Jesus Christ', 'Connection of Apostolic Authority', 'This connection highlights Paul''s role as an apostle, emphasizing his calling and the ministry he received. Both passages reflect the theme of being enabled and appointed by Christ for service.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 1, 60, 1, 3, 3, 'which is our hope', 'Connection of Hope in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of hope associated with Jesus Christ. In 1 Timothy, Paul refers to Jesus as ''our hope,'' while 1 Peter speaks of a ''lively hope'' through His resurrection.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 2, 56, 1, 4, 4, 'my own son in the faith', 'Connection Between Timothy and Titus', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the author and the recipient, referring to them as ''my own son'' in faith. Additionally, they both include the phrase ''Grace, mercy, and peace'' from God and Jesus Christ, highlighting a common greeting structure.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 2, 55, 1, 2, 2, 'Grace, mercy, and peace', 'Connection of Greetings to Timothy', 'Both passages emphasize a personal relationship with Timothy, referring to him as ''my own son'' and ''my dearly beloved son.'' They also share the same greeting of ''Grace, mercy, and peace'' from God and Christ, highlighting a consistent message of support.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 2, 46, 4, 14, 17, NULL, 'Father-Son Relationship in Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the father-son relationship in faith, with Paul referring to Timothy as his ''beloved son'' in both contexts. This connection highlights the role of Timothy as a spiritual son and faithful messenger of Paul''s teachings.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 2, 50, 2, 19, 22, 'my own son in the faith', 'Connection Between Timothy''s Role', 'Both passages emphasize Timothy''s relationship as a son and servant. In 1 Timothy, he is referred to as ''my own son in the faith,'' while Philippians describes him as ''a son with the father'' who serves in the gospel.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 2, 44, 16, 1, 3, 'my own son in the faith', 'Connection between Timothy''s Identity', 'Both passages emphasize Timothy''s role as a disciple. In 1 Timothy, Paul refers to Timothy as ''my own son in the faith,'' while Acts identifies him as a disciple in Lystra, highlighting their close relationship.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 2, 45, 1, 7, 7, 'Grace, mercy, and peace', 'Grace and Peace Connection', 'Both passages emphasize grace and peace from God the Father and Jesus Christ. This connection highlights a shared greeting structure that reinforces the importance of these themes in the early Christian community.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 2, 55, 2, 1, 1, 'grace', 'Connection of Grace in Timothy', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of grace. In 1 Timothy, grace is a greeting, while in 2 Timothy, it is a source of strength for Timothy.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 3, 48, 1, 6, 7, 'teach no other doctrine', 'Warning Against False Teachings', 'This connection highlights the concern for maintaining sound doctrine. Both passages emphasize the danger of teaching ''another doctrine'' or ''another gospel'' that distorts the true message.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 3, 54, 6, 3, 3, 'teach no other doctrine', 'Teaching Sound Doctrine', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of teaching sound doctrine. In 1 Timothy 1:3, the charge is to teach no other doctrine, while 1 Timothy 6:3 warns against teaching otherwise and highlights the necessity of wholesome words.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 3, 63, 1, 9, 10, 'teach no other doctrine', 'Doctrine and Teaching Connection', 'This connection highlights the importance of adhering to sound doctrine. Both passages emphasize the necessity of teaching and abiding in the correct doctrine to maintain a relationship with God.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 3, 56, 1, 9, 11, 'teach no other doctrine', 'Doctrine and False Teaching', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of sound doctrine and the need to confront false teachings. In 1 Timothy, the charge is to teach no other doctrine, while Titus highlights the necessity of holding fast to the faithful word to counter unruly talkers.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 3, 44, 20, 1, 3, 'when I went into Macedonia', 'Paul''s Journey to Macedonia', 'This connection highlights Paul''s journey to Macedonia in both passages. In 1 Timothy, Paul instructs Timothy regarding Ephesus after his departure to Macedonia, while Acts recounts Paul''s travels through Macedonia following an uproar.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 3, 51, 2, 6, 11, 'teach no other doctrine', 'Warning Against False Teachings', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of adhering to true doctrine and warn against teachings that deviate from Christ. In 1 Timothy, the charge is to teach no other doctrine, while Colossians cautions against being spoiled by philosophy and deceit. This connection highlights the need for faithfulness to the teachings of Christ.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 3, 54, 4, 6, 6, 'teach no other doctrine', 'Connection of Doctrine and Teaching', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of sound doctrine and teaching within the church. The first verse warns against teaching other doctrines, while the second encourages reminding the brethren of good doctrine.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 4, 54, 4, 7, 7, 'fables', 'Connection of Fables and Godliness', 'Both passages emphasize the rejection of fables and the importance of godliness. They highlight the need to focus on spiritual edification rather than distractions that lead to questions.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 4, 56, 1, 14, 14, 'fables', 'Connection of Fables and Truth', 'Both passages emphasize the rejection of fables and teachings that distract from the truth. They warn against teachings that lead away from faith and sound doctrine.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 4, 56, 3, 9, 9, 'genealogies', 'Connection Between Genealogies and Questions', 'Both passages emphasize the avoidance of genealogies and foolish questions, highlighting their unprofitable nature. This connection underscores a shared concern for focusing on faith rather than distractions.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 4, 55, 4, 4, 4, 'fables', 'Connection Between Fables and Truth', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of fables, highlighting a shift away from truth. 1 Timothy warns against fables that lead to questions, while 2 Timothy describes a turning away from truth towards fables.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 4, 61, 1, 16, 16, 'fables', 'Connection of Fables and Truth', 'Both passages emphasize the rejection of fables. 1 Timothy warns against ''fables and endless genealogies,'' while 2 Peter asserts they have not followed ''cunningly devised fables.'' This connection highlights a shared concern for truth in teaching.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 4, 54, 6, 3, 5, NULL, 'Connection of False Teachings', 'Both passages emphasize the dangers of engaging in unproductive discussions and disputes. They warn against teachings that lead to strife rather than godly edification.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 4, 55, 2, 14, 14, NULL, 'Focus on Profitable Teaching', 'This connection highlights the emphasis on avoiding distractions that do not edify faith. Both passages caution against engaging in discussions that lead to confusion rather than spiritual growth.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 5, 54, 1, 19, 19, 'good conscience', 'Faith and Conscience Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of ''faith'' and ''good conscience'' in the Christian life. The first verse introduces these concepts as foundational, while the second warns against neglecting them, leading to spiritual failure.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 5, 48, 5, 22, 22, 'charity out of a pure heart', 'Connection of Love and Charity', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of love, with 1 Timothy highlighting ''charity'' as the ultimate goal of commandment, while Galatians lists ''love'' as the first fruit of the Spirit. This connection highlights the centrality of love in Christian ethics.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 5, 48, 5, 13, 14, 'charity out of a pure heart', 'Connection of Love and Service', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of love as a guiding principle in Christian conduct. 1 Timothy highlights charity from a pure heart, while Galatians connects love to serving one another, suggesting that genuine love fulfills the law.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 5, 55, 2, 22, 22, 'charity out of a pure heart', 'Connection of Pure Heart and Charity', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of a pure heart and charity. 1 Timothy 1:5 mentions charity out of a pure heart, while 2 Timothy 2:22 calls for following charity with those who have a pure heart.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 5, 55, 1, 5, 5, 'faith unfeigned', 'Connection of Unfeigned Faith', 'Both passages emphasize ''faith unfeigned'' as a central theme. The first verse highlights the importance of genuine faith, while the second verse recalls the unfeigned faith present in Timothy''s family.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 5, 41, 12, 28, 34, 'charity out of a pure heart', 'Connection of Love and Commandments', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of love, with 1 Timothy highlighting ''charity out of a pure heart'' and Mark focusing on loving God and neighbor. This connection highlights the centrality of love in fulfilling God''s commandments.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 5, 60, 1, 22, 22, 'charity out of a pure heart', 'Connection of Pure Heart and Love', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of love stemming from a pure heart. They highlight the necessity of unfeigned love and a good conscience as foundational to Christian conduct.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 6, 56, 1, 10, 10, 'vain jangling', 'Connection of Vain Talkers', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of ''vain'' talkers who lead others astray. This connection highlights the theme of false teachings and their impact on the community.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 6, 55, 2, 23, 24, 'vain jangling', 'Avoiding Strife and Vain Jangling', 'This connection highlights the theme of avoiding unproductive discussions. Both passages emphasize the importance of steering clear of strife and focusing on constructive teaching.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 6, 54, 6, 20, 21, 'vain jangling', 'Connection of Vain Jangling', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of ''vain'' discussions that lead believers astray. The first warns against ''vain jangling,'' while the second cautions Timothy to avoid ''profane and vain babblings.''', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 6, 56, 3, 9, 9, 'vain jangling', 'Connection of Vain Teachings', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of engaging in unproductive discussions and teachings. They warn against distractions that lead believers away from sound doctrine, highlighting the unprofitable nature of such pursuits.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 6, 54, 5, 15, 15, 'turned aside', 'Turning Aside Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of turning aside, with the first mentioning ''swerved'' and the second stating ''turned aside.'' This connection highlights a thematic warning against deviation from the faith.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 6, 55, 4, 10, 10, 'turned aside unto vain jangling', 'Departure from Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of individuals turning away from their commitments. In 1 Timothy, some have ''turned aside unto vain jangling,'' while in 2 Timothy, Demas ''hath forsaken'' Paul, indicating a similar departure from faithfulness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 7, 45, 1, 22, 22, 'understanding neither what they say', 'Wisdom and Understanding in Error', 'Both passages emphasize a lack of true understanding. In 1 Timothy, those desiring to teach the law do not grasp its meaning, while in Romans, those who claim wisdom are revealed as fools.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 7, 61, 2, 12, 12, 'understanding neither what they say', 'Understanding and Ignorance of Truth', 'Both passages emphasize a lack of understanding regarding the truth. In 1 Timothy, the teachers do not understand what they affirm, while in 2 Peter, the brute beasts speak evil of things they understand not.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 7, 54, 6, 4, 4, 'understanding neither what they say', 'Pride and Ignorance in Teaching', 'Both passages emphasize the dangers of pride and ignorance in teaching. The first warns against those who desire to teach without understanding, while the second describes a proud individual who knows nothing and engages in strife.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 7, 48, 3, 5, 5, 'understanding neither what they say', 'Understanding Law and Faith', 'This connection highlights the contrast between those who desire to teach the law without understanding and the question of whether miracles are performed by the law or faith. Both passages emphasize the importance of true understanding in relation to the law and faith.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 7, 48, 5, 3, 4, 'understanding neither what they say', 'Connection of Law and Understanding', 'This connection highlights the theme of misunderstanding the law. Both passages emphasize the consequences of misapplying the law, as those desiring to teach it lack understanding, leading to a fall from grace for those justified by it.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 7, 45, 2, 19, 21, 'teachers of the law', 'Teachers of the Law Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of teachers of the law and their lack of understanding. 1 Timothy highlights those desiring to teach without comprehension, while Romans questions the self-awareness of those who instruct others yet fail to apply the law to themselves.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 7, 55, 3, 7, 7, 'understanding neither what they say', 'Knowledge and Understanding in Teaching', 'Both passages emphasize a lack of true understanding. In 1 Timothy, teachers do not comprehend what they affirm, while in 2 Timothy, learners are ever learning but fail to grasp the truth.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 8, 45, 7, 12, 13, 'the law is good', 'Law''s Goodness and Purpose', 'Both passages emphasize the law''s goodness and its role in revealing sin. 1 Timothy states the law is good when used lawfully, while Romans affirms the law as holy and good, highlighting its purpose in exposing sin. This connection highlights the positive nature of the law in relation to human behavior.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 8, 19, 19, 7, 10, 'the law is good', 'Connection of Law''s Goodness', 'This connection highlights the goodness of the law in both passages. 1 Timothy emphasizes the lawful use of the law, while Psalms extols the law''s perfection and its ability to convert the soul.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 8, 55, 2, 5, 5, 'lawfully', 'Lawful Striving in Faith', 'This connection highlights the importance of lawful conduct in both passages. 1 Timothy emphasizes using the law lawfully, while 2 Timothy stresses striving lawfully for mastery.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 8, 19, 119, 127, 128, 'the law is good', 'Law and Commandments Connection', 'This connection highlights the value of the law and commandments. Both passages emphasize the goodness and rightness of God''s instructions, suggesting a deep respect for divine precepts.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 8, 48, 3, 21, 21, 'the law is good', 'Law''s Role in Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the law''s goodness and its limitations. Both passages emphasize that while the law is good, it cannot provide life or righteousness on its own.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 8, 16, 9, 13, 13, 'law is good', 'Connection of Law and Goodness', 'Both passages emphasize the goodness of the law. 1 Timothy highlights the lawful use of the law, while Nehemiah describes the laws as good statutes and commandments.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 8, 45, 7, 22, 22, 'the law is good', 'Delight in the Law', 'This connection highlights the positive view of the law in both passages. 1 Timothy emphasizes the law''s goodness when used properly, while Romans expresses a delight in the law of God, indicating a shared appreciation for its value.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 9, 48, 3, 19, 19, 'for the lawless and disobedient', 'Purpose of the Law', 'This connection highlights the purpose of the law in addressing transgressions and guiding the lawless. Both passages emphasize that the law serves to identify and restrain sin until the promise is fulfilled.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 9, 60, 4, 18, 18, NULL, 'Connection of Righteous and Ungodly', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between the righteous and the ungodly. 1 Timothy highlights the law''s purpose for the lawless, while 1 Peter questions the fate of the ungodly and sinner in contrast to the scarcely saved righteous.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 9, 45, 5, 20, 20, 'the law is not made for a righteous man', 'Law and Grace Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the law in relation to sin and righteousness. 1 Timothy highlights that the law is for the lawless, while Romans discusses how the law reveals sin, leading to an abundance of grace.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 9, 48, 3, 10, 14, 'the law is not made for a righteous man', 'Connection Between Law and Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the law in relation to righteousness. 1 Timothy highlights that the law is for the lawless, while Galatians states that no one is justified by the law, indicating a contrast between law and faith.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 9, 56, 3, 3, 3, 'disobedient', 'Connection of Law and Disobedience', 'Both passages emphasize the condition of being disobedient and ungodly. 1 Timothy 1:9 describes the law''s purpose for the lawless, while Titus 3:3 reflects on past disobedience and foolishness, illustrating the need for the law.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 9, 45, 1, 30, 30, 'disobedient', 'Connection of Law and Disobedience', 'Both passages emphasize disobedience and lawlessness. 1 Timothy identifies the law''s purpose for the disobedient, while Romans lists disobedience among various sinful behaviors.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 9, 1, 9, 5, 6, 'for the lawless and disobedient', 'Connection Between Law and Justice', 'This connection highlights the theme of accountability for wrongdoing. Both passages emphasize the consequences for lawlessness and the sanctity of human life, indicating that the law serves to address the actions of the ungodly.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 10, 3, 18, 22, 22, 'defile themselves with mankind', 'Connection on Sexual Morality', 'Both passages emphasize prohibitions against immoral sexual behavior. 1 Timothy 1:10 includes ''defile themselves with mankind,'' which directly relates to the condemnation of same-sex relations in Leviticus 18:22.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 10, 46, 6, 9, 10, NULL, 'Connection of Unrighteousness', 'Both passages emphasize behaviors that exclude individuals from the kingdom of God. They list similar categories of immoral actions, highlighting the seriousness of these offenses against sound doctrine.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 10, 45, 1, 26, 26, 'contrary to sound doctrine', 'Connection of Moral Deviation', 'Both passages emphasize behaviors that are contrary to sound doctrine and natural use. 1 Timothy lists various immoral actions, while Romans describes a deviation from natural relations, highlighting a theme of moral corruption.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 10, 55, 4, 3, 3, 'contrary to sound doctrine', 'Connection of Sound Doctrine', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of sound doctrine and warn against behaviors contrary to it. 1 Timothy lists various immoral actions, while 2 Timothy predicts a time when people will reject sound doctrine for their own desires.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 10, 48, 5, 19, 21, 'contrary to sound doctrine', 'Connection of Moral Conduct', 'Both passages emphasize behaviors that are contrary to sound doctrine and the works of the flesh. They list immoral actions, highlighting the consequences of such behaviors in relation to inheriting the kingdom of God.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 10, 66, 21, 27, 27, NULL, 'Connection of Defilement and Lies', 'Both passages emphasize the exclusion of those who defile themselves or make lies from the presence of God. This connection highlights the moral standards set forth in scripture regarding behavior contrary to sound doctrine.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 10, 54, 6, 3, 3, 'contrary to sound doctrine', 'Connection of Sound Doctrine', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of sound doctrine and wholesome words. The first passage lists behaviors contrary to sound doctrine, while the second warns against teaching otherwise.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 11, 48, 2, 7, 7, 'committed to my trust', 'Gospel Commitment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the commitment of the gospel to specific individuals. 1 Timothy highlights the trust placed in Paul regarding the gospel, while Galatians speaks to the specific assignment of the gospel to him and Peter.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 11, 56, 1, 3, 3, 'committed to my trust', 'Connection of Gospel Commitment', 'Both passages emphasize the commitment of the gospel and God''s word to the speaker. This connection highlights the responsibility entrusted to them in preaching.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 11, 54, 6, 15, 15, 'blessed God', 'Connection of the Blessed God', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of the ''blessed'' nature of God. In 1 Timothy 1:11, God is referred to as the ''blessed God,'' while in 1 Timothy 6:15, He is described as ''the blessed and only Potentate.'' This connection highlights the divine authority and glory attributed to God.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 11, 45, 2, 16, 16, NULL, 'Connection of the Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''my gospel,'' linking the message of salvation and divine judgment. This connection highlights the continuity of the gospel''s significance in both the proclamation and the ultimate judgment of God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 11, 47, 4, 4, 4, 'glorious gospel', 'Connection of the Glorious Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the ''glorious gospel,'' highlighting its significance in revealing divine truth. The first passage speaks of the gospel committed to trust, while the second discusses its role in illuminating minds blinded by the god of this world.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 11, 47, 5, 18, 20, 'committed to my trust', 'Ministry of Reconciliation', 'Both passages emphasize the commitment to the gospel and the ministry of reconciliation. 1 Timothy speaks of the gospel being committed to Paul, while 2 Corinthians discusses the ministry and word of reconciliation entrusted to believers.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 11, 19, 138, 2, 2, 'glorious gospel of the blessed God', 'Connection of Gospel and Word', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of God''s word and truth. 1 Timothy highlights the gospel as a glorious trust, while Psalms magnifies God''s word above all. This connection highlights the reverence for divine communication.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 12, 50, 4, 13, 13, NULL, 'Strength Through Christ Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of empowerment through Christ. Both passages emphasize the ability to serve and accomplish tasks through the strength provided by Christ.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(54, 1, 12, 55, 4, 17, 17, 'enabled me, for that he counted me faithful', 'Strength and Ministry Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of divine support in ministry. In 1 Timothy, Paul thanks Christ for enabling him for ministry, while in 2 Timothy, he acknowledges the Lord''s strength during his preaching efforts.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
